explanation:
The Madurai City (Traffic) Police have planned to install audio signals in at least 20 locations, to enable the visually challenged persons to cross intersections without any difficulty. The facility is presently available in Chennai. The signals would be launched in a phased manner from this week at major intersections. The visually challenged could also cross without any hassle as they could hear the instructions in both Tamil and English. The audio would be available for 60 to 90 seconds.
